                        </title>
            </info>
            <imagedata fileref="images/light_switch_230_statechart_editor_change_state_name_03.png" />
           </imageobject>
          </inlinemediaobject>
         </entry>
        </row>
        <row>
         <entry>
                  However, since the state box’s size is smaller now than before while the box’s left position remains unchanged, the graph looks crooked.
                </entry>
         <entry></entry>
        </row>
        <row>
         <entry>
                  We can improve it by dragging the state box a little bit to the right. When it is centered below the initial state symbol, a vertical blue line appears giving the user a visual hint:
                </entry>
         <entry>
          <inlinemediaobject>
           <imageobject>
            <info>
             <title>
                          Changing a state's name [4]
                        </title>
            </info>
            <imagedata fileref="images/light_switch_230_statechart_editor_change_state_name_04.png" />
           </imageobject>
          </inlinemediaobject>
         </entry>
        </row>
        <row>
